    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_4_694-753",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "694-753",
      "markText": "另一种途径就是发明许多技艺（arts），通过它们来利用自然的力量；人就从威胁着他的那些条件和力量本身中构成了一座堡垒。",
      "totalCount": 108,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=694&rangeEnd=753",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=694&rangeEnd=753"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_4_952-1015",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "952-1015",
      "markText": "一直很少有人预示过，人类可以借助于技艺来控制自然的力量与法则，以建立一个秩序、正义和美丽的王国，而且也很少有人注意到这样的人。",
      "totalCount": 108,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=952&rangeEnd=1015",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=952&rangeEnd=1015"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_6_8980-9071",
      "chapterUid": 6,
      "range": "8980-9071",
      "markText": "笛卡尔企图在能知的心灵内部去寻求绝对确定性的所在；他一方面排除了古代人试想在外在世界上去发现这种绝对确定性的企图，另一方面排除了中世纪人试想在外在的天启中去寻求这种绝对确定性的企图。",
      "totalCount": 108,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=6&rangeStart=8980&rangeEnd=9071",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=6&rangeStart=8980&rangeEnd=9071"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_4_3931-4084",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "3931-4084",
      "markText": "因为人们所不喜欢的不是不确定性的本身，而是由于不确定性使我们有陷入恶果的危险。",
      "totalCount": 105,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=3931&rangeEnd=4084",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=3931&rangeEnd=4084"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_4_1167-1202",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "1167-1202",
      "markText": "哲学家们推崇过改变个人观念的方法，而宗教导师们则推崇改变内心感情的方法",
      "totalCount": 104,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=1167&rangeEnd=1202",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=1167&rangeEnd=1202"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_4_2968-3014",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "2968-3014",
      "markText": "人之不能自信，使得他欲求解脱和超脱自我；而他以为在纯粹的知识中，他能达到这个超越自我的境界。",
      "totalCount": 100,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=2968&rangeEnd=3014",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=2968&rangeEnd=3014"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_6_3722-3814",
      "chapterUid": 6,
      "range": "3722-3814",
      "markText": "他更加完全地表现出他对希伯来传统的本质要素的忠心诚意（相信最后的和自足的实有乃是一切人类思想和行动的标准），并且保持着希腊的认识论，崇尚理性优越于经验，而同时又热烈地坚持新科学的自然观",
      "totalCount": 98,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=6&rangeStart=3722&rangeEnd=3814",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=6&rangeStart=3722&rangeEnd=3814"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_4_2612-2654",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "2612-2654",
      "markText": "人们把纯理智和理智活动提升到实际事务之上，这是与他们寻求绝对不变的确定性根本联系着的",
      "totalCount": 96,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=2612&rangeEnd=2654",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=2612&rangeEnd=2654"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_4_10007-10086",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "10007-10086",
      "markText": "哲学把这种主张理性化了。它不再借助于仪礼和祭祀来求得解脱，而是通过理性求得解脱。这种解脱是一种理智上的、理论上的事情，构成它的那种知识是离开实践活动而获得的。",
      "totalCount": 90,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=10007&rangeEnd=10086",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=10007&rangeEnd=10086"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_5_630-676",
      "chapterUid": 5,
      "range": "630-676",
      "markText": "由于缺乏知识，或不能完全保证，我们才有信仰。",
      "totalCount": 88,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=5&rangeStart=630&rangeEnd=676",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=5&rangeStart=630&rangeEnd=676"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_4_2736-2758",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "2736-2758",
      "markText": "通过思维，人们却似乎可以逃避不确定性的危险。",
      "totalCount": 85,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=2736&rangeEnd=2758",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=2736&rangeEnd=2758"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_4_13287-13309",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "13287-13309",
      "markText": "确定性的寻求已经支配着我们的根本的形而上学。",
      "totalCount": 85,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=13287&rangeEnd=13309",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=13287&rangeEnd=13309"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_11_12682-12720",
      "chapterUid": 11,
      "range": "12682-12720",
      "markText": "这种主张肯定是现象必须遵守普遍法则的这种见解的产物，而后者又是牛顿哲学的遗传",
      "totalCount": 85,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=27020156&chapterUid=11&rangeStart=12682&rangeEnd=12720",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/3c532e70719c4b7c3c571af?chapterUid=11&rangeStart=12682&rangeEnd=12720"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "27020156_4_3082-3154",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "3082-3154",
